================================================================================
KNOWN ISSUES AND WORKAROUNDS APPLIED
================================================================================

  Issue 1: v4-migrator 5.0.1 preflight expects Flyway head '202605111028'
           but the apiserver 5.0.1 jar contains 13 migrations up to '202606080956'.
  Fix    : Insert Flyway history rows 1-6 only before running extract/transform/load.
           Insert rows 7-13 after load completes, before starting the apiserver.

  Issue 2: VULNERABILITYMETRICS converted from table to materialized view in
           V202605311738, but the migrator tries to INSERT into it as a table.
  Fix    : Drop the materialized view and create a plain table before load.
           Restore the materialized view by re-running V202605311738 after load.

  Issue 3: Migrator loads USER before PERMISSION, violating FK constraints.
  Fix    : Drop USERS_PERMISSIONS_PERMISSION_FK, USERS_PERMISSIONS_USER_FK, and
           TEAMS_PERMISSIONS_PERMISSION_FK before load. Restore after.

  Issue 4: v4 permission IDs (1-41) do not exist in v5 (v5 seeds IDs 43-84).
  Fix    : Delete USERS_PERMISSIONS and TEAMS_PERMISSIONS rows where PERMISSION_ID < 43
           after the apiserver seeds permissions on first boot.

  Issue 5: Apiserver seeds admin user and other data on every boot, causing
           migrator preflight "table not empty" failures.
  Fix    : Never start the apiserver between schema init and load. If it boots
           accidentally, truncate all affected tables with session_replication_role
           = replica before retrying load.


